SIMPLE: schooling
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Schooling
<hw>School"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Instruction in
school; tuition; education in an institution of learning; act of
teaching.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Discipline; reproof; reprimand; <as>as, he gave his
son a good <ex>schooling</ex></as>.</def> <rj><au>Sir W.
Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Compensation for instruction; price or reward paid
to an instructor for teaching pupils.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Schooling</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Schooling
<hw>School"ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See <er>School</er> a
shoal.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Collecting or running in schools
or shoals.</def><-- used of fish -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Schooling</qex> species like the herring and menhaden.</q>
<rj><qau>G. B. Goode.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Schoolma'am</ent>⟦br⟧
